Program: Omnibus
Title: On the Trail of Butch and Sundance
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376lqf
Last Broadcast Date: 06 July 1998
They looked like ‘Bob Hoskins crossed with Hugh Grant’ and ‘Cary Grant as a bowlegged cowboy’. Uncovering the true story of the American outlaws Robert Leroy Parker and Harry Longabaugh, better known as Butch and Sundance, on a visit to Bolivia. Contributors include historians Anne Meadows and Dan Buck Presented by British author, John Pilkington. Show less